BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 176.4 720 Td (Chapter 2: The Food Factory) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Nano slid down a long, dark, squishy tube. 'This must be the esophagus!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (SPLASH! He landed in a pool of bubbling liquid. 'Welcome to the stomach!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (The walls around him were squeezing and churning like a washing machine.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('This is where food gets broken into tiny pieces!' Nano observed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (Strong acid and special chemicals called enzymes dissolved everything around him.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('Time to move on before I get dissolved too!' Nano laughed nervously.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: YOUR STOMACH) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Your stomach is like a muscular bag that churns and mixes food with acid.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Stomach acid is so strong it could dissolve metal! But a special lining protects you.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Enzymes are like tiny scissors that cut food into smaller and smaller pieces.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Food stays in your stomach for 2-5 hours, being broken down into a soupy mixture.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (After the stomach, food moves to the small intestine where nutrients are absorbed.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* Your stomach can hold about 1 liter of food \(like a large water bottle\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* The stomach lining replaces itself every 3-4 days to avoid being dissolved!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Rumbling sounds happen when your stomach squeezes air and liquid together.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Put a piece of bread in a zip bag with a little vinegar. Squeeze it - that is like digestion!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (Why does your stomach make growling noises when you are hungry?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
