BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 171.6 720 Td (Chapter 3: The River of Life) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Nano squeezed through the stomach wall and found himself in a rushing river!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('This is your blood!' Nano exclaimed, amazed by the red flowing river.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (Tiny red discs zoomed past him like millions of delivery trucks.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('Those are red blood cells! They carry oxygen to every part of your body!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (White blob-like cells patrolled the area like police officers on duty.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('And those are white blood cells - your body's defense soldiers!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: YOUR BLOOD) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Blood is made of plasma \(liquid\), red blood cells, white blood cells, and platelets.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Red blood cells carry oxygen from your lungs to every cell in your body.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (White blood cells fight germs, bacteria, and viruses that try to make you sick.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Platelets are tiny cell fragments that help stop bleeding when you get a cut.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (You have about 25 trillion red blood cells in your body right now!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* If you lined up all your blood vessels, they would stretch 60,000 miles!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* A single drop of blood contains about 5 million red blood cells.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Your body makes about 2 million new red blood cells every single second!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Look at the veins on the inside of your wrist. That blue color is blood returning to your heart!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (Why do you think blood looks red when it carries oxygen?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
