BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 133.20000000000002 720 Td (Chapter 4: The Pump That Never Stops) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (The blood river carried Nano to the most powerful muscle in the body.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (THUMP-THUMP! THUMP-THUMP! The sound was deafening!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('The heart!' Nano shouted over the rhythmic pounding.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (He watched as blood flowed in and out of four amazing chambers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (The right side pumped blood to the lungs, the left side to the whole body.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('This incredible pump beats 100,000 times every single day!' Nano marveled.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: YOUR HEART) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Your heart is about the size of your fist and weighs less than a pound.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (It has four chambers: two atria \(top\) receive blood, two ventricles \(bottom\) pump it out.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (The right side sends blood to your lungs to pick up oxygen.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (The left side pumps oxygen-rich blood to every cell in your body.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Your heart beats about 100,000 times per day - that is 35 million times a year!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* A child's heart beats about 80-100 times per minute.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* Your heart pumps about 2,000 gallons of blood every day!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* The heart starts beating about 4 weeks after a baby starts growing.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Put your hand on your chest and count heartbeats for 15 seconds. Multiply by 4 for your heart rate!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (Why does your heart beat faster when you exercise?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
