BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 152.4 720 Td (Chapter 5: The Breathing Machine) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Nano rode the bloodstream up into two enormous, spongy pink organs.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('The lungs!' he exclaimed. 'This is where blood picks up fresh oxygen!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (Millions of tiny air sacs called alveoli surrounded him like clusters of grapes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (He watched oxygen molecules jump from the air into the blood cells.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (At the same time, carbon dioxide waste jumped out of the blood into the air sacs.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('It is like a perfect trade!' Nano said. 'Oxygen in, carbon dioxide out!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: YOUR LUNGS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (You breathe about 20,000 times every day without even thinking about it!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Your lungs have 300 million alveoli \(tiny air sacs\) for gas exchange.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (The diaphragm is a dome-shaped muscle under your lungs that helps you breathe.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (When you breathe in, oxygen goes into blood. When you breathe out, CO2 leaves.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (If you spread out all your alveoli flat, they would cover a tennis court!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* You breathe in about 11,000 liters of air every single day.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* Your right lung is slightly bigger than your left \(to make room for your heart\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Yawning helps get extra oxygen when your body needs it.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Breathe onto a cold mirror - the fog is water vapor leaving your lungs!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (Why do you breathe faster when you run? What does your body need more of?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
