BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 166.8 720 Td (Chapter 6: The Command Center) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Nano traveled up through blood vessels into the most amazing organ of all.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('The brain!' he whispered in awe. 'The command center of the entire body!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (Billions of tiny cells called neurons were firing signals like lightning bolts.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (Messages zoomed along at 270 miles per hour in every direction!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('This is where you think, dream, remember, feel emotions, and control everything!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (Nano watched as different areas handled seeing, hearing, moving, and thinking.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: YOUR BRAIN) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Your brain has about 86 billion neurons \(nerve cells\) that communicate with each other.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Neurons send electrical signals to each other at speeds up to 270 miles per hour!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Different parts of the brain control different things: movement, vision, language, emotions.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Your brain uses 20% of your body's energy, even though it is only 2% of your weight.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (The brain is always active, even when you sleep - that is when it organizes memories!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* Your brain generates enough electricity to power a small light bulb!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* The brain cannot feel pain - it has no pain receptors!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Your brain is about 73% water. Staying hydrated helps you think better!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Try rubbing your belly in circles while patting your head. Your brain controls both at once!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (How does your brain know to keep your heart beating while you sleep?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
