BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 186.0 720 Td (Chapter 8: Growing Strong) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Nano's last stop was the bones and muscles that give your body its shape.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('Your skeleton is like a building's frame!' Nano explained to Alex.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (He watched muscles pulling on bones like puppet strings, making Alex move.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('Muscles always work in pairs - one pulls while the other relaxes!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (Nano looked at all the amazing things he had seen and smiled.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('Alex, your body is truly the most incredible machine ever made!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: BONES AND MUSCLES) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (You have 206 bones in your body \(babies have about 270 - some fuse together!\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Bones are alive! They have blood vessels inside and grow as you grow.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (You have over 600 muscles that help you move, from tiny eye muscles to big leg muscles.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Muscles work in pairs: biceps bends your arm, triceps straightens it.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Your strongest muscle is your jaw muscle \(masseter\) - it can bite with 200 lbs of force!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 14 Tf 72 444 Td (MORAL:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F5 13 Tf 72 424 Td (Your body is the most incredible machine ever made - take care of it!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 408 Td (Eat healthy food, exercise, sleep well, and drink plenty of water.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 324 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 383 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 363 Td (* The smallest bone is in your ear \(stirrup\) - smaller than a grain of rice!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 345 Td (* Your body replaces all its bone cells every 7-10 years.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 327 Td (* Smiling uses 17 muscles; frowning uses 43. Smiling is easier!) Tj ET

endstream
